benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Remove tags from payment

covered: Valid Deletion: Multiple scenarios ensure deletion works (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05).
Input validation and errors: invalid paymentId format (TC06), non-existent payment (TC07), invalid tagDef value (TC09).
Authorization and header handling: missing required header (TC08), unauthorized access (TC11).
Error handling and service availability: service unavailable (TC12), timeout (TC22).
Input parameter validation and edge cases: extra query parameter (TC14), large number of tagDef (TC15), injection attack (TC13).
Data integrity and auditing: data consistency after removal (TC21), integration with audit logging (TC20).
Concurrency and performance: concurrent removals (TC16), high load performance (TC17).
Regression and compatibility: regression test (TC18), backward compatibility (TC19).
Regression/scenario coverage for proper removal state and GET-after-remove (TC21).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Authorization depth: No explicit 403 coverage or role-based access variation.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No tests for rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Additional 5xx scenarios: Only 503 tested; no 500 internal server or other 5xx variants.
Soft-delete semantics: No explicit test distinguishing hard delete vs soft delete.
Edge-case data sizes: no tests for extremely large tag sets beyond TC15.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination behavior when listing/removing tags across large result sets.
Introduce tests to validate caching headers and reuse behavior (ETag/Cache-Control).
Add authorization depth tests (e.g., different roles, 403 responses).
Add rate-limiting/throttling scenarios to ensure stability under rapid consecutive requests.
Include 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to validate server-side error handling beyond 503, and confirm proper messaging.
Clarify/cover soft-delete semantics if applicable and ensure consistency with GET state.
